  "guide.avoidminer.page_1": "AVOID MINER GUIDE\n\nWelcome to the Avoid Miner mod.\n\nThis guide covers machines, improvements, recipes, and mechanics.\n\nContents:\n1) Overview\n2) Energy and slots\n3) World modes\n4) Enchant modes\n5) Upgrade drops\n6) Recipes",
  "guide.avoidminer.page_2": "OVERVIEW\n\nAvoid Miners are automatic machines that burn fuel, store energy, and generate resources.\n\nFeatures:\n- Three machine tiers\n- 27 output slots\n- Mining, Energy, and Speed improvements\n- World modes: Overworld, Botany, Nether\n- Hopper support",
  "guide.avoidminer.page_3": "ENERGY AND FULL OUTPUT\n\nFuel becomes internal energy.\nThe machine consumes energy while generating.\n\nIf all 27 output slots contain at least one item, the machine pauses and shows FULL. It resumesafter at least one output slot is emptied.",
  "guide.avoidminer.page_4": "WORLD MODES\n\nOverworld: generates normal mining resources.\n\nBotany: generates plant resources instead of ores.\n\nNether: generates quartz, gold nuggets, and ancient debris. With Silk Touch, quartz and nuggets become Nether ore blocks.",
  "guide.avoidminer.page_5": "ENCHANT MODES\n\nFortune: multiplies Overworld and Nether outputs from x1 to x4, except ancient debris.\n\nSilk Touch: converts mining outputs into ore blocks. Botany outputs are not changed.",
  "guide.avoidminer.page_6": "UPGRADE DROPS\n\nUpgrade T2:\nGeneratedby Avoid Miner T1 in Nether mode. Chance: 0.5%.\n\nUpgrade T3:\nGeneratedby Avoid Miner T2 with Nether + Fortune modifiers at the same time. Chance: 0.5%.",
  "guide.avoidminer.page_7": "IMPROVEMENTS\n\nMining Upgrade: increases success chance.\nT1 x1.5 | T2 x1.7 | T3 x2.0\n\nEnergy Upgrade: reduces energy use.\nT1 x0.8 | T2 x0.7 | T3 x0.6\n\nSpeed Upgrade: reduces cycle time.\nT1 /1.5 | T2 /1.7 | T3 /2.0",
  "guide.avoidminer.page_8": "TIPS\n\n- Use hoppers for fuel input and item output.\n- Speed + Mining increases production strongly.\n- Fortune does not affect ancient debris.\n- Silk Touch is theway to get ore blocks from generated resources.\n- Empty one output slot to restart a full machine.",

